snippet: Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, the Burmese democracy leader, says she “never doubted” that her first trip abroad after a long house arrest would be to Norway.
abstract: Burmese democracy leader Daw Aung San Suu Kyi arrives in Norway to finally deliver the Nobel lecture for the peace price she won in 1991.
lead_paragraph: Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, the Burmese democracy leader, says she “never doubted” that her first trip abroad after a long house arrest would be to Norway.

headline.seo: Burmese Leader Reaches Oslo 21 Years After Winning Nobel
headline.main: 21 Years After Winning Nobel, Democracy Leader Reaches Oslo
headline.print_headline: Burma Leader Reaches Oslo 21 Years Later
